Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Drain the @mozzarella{1} and pat it dry with #kitchen paper{}, making sure you squeeze out as much liquid as possible. Then tear it into pieces.

Pop your @pizza bases{2} onto a #board{}. Spread the @marinara sauce{120%g} over the pizza bases, leaving a 1cm border around the edge. Top with the @chorizo slices{75%g}, then the @black olives{30}. Scatter over the torn mozzarella.

When the oven is hot, bake the pizzas directly on the middle shelf until the base is golden and the cheese has melted and is bubbly, ~{10-12%minutes}.

While the pizzas cook, finish off the washing up and take a break until it's time to make the chilli honey drizzle.

Just before the pizzas are ready, pour the @honey{15%g} into a #small saucepan{}. Add the @chilli flakes{1} (only use a pinch, they're hot!), then pop it on low heat and bring up to a gentle simmer for ~{1-2%minutes}. It should be a drizzling consistency.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

> TIP: Don't do this too early or the honey will harden as it cools.

When ready, remove the pizzas from the oven and transfer them to a board. Drizzle over the chilli honey (this can be left off for any little ones). Dress the @wild rocket{20%g} with a little @?olive oil{} if you'd like, then pop on top of the pizza and cut into slices. Transfer to your plates and dig in. Enjoy!